The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks for time series analysis and prediction, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the learning of network architecture, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of neural networks for prediction and function approximation is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the method to robotic soccer falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of neural networks for time series analysis and prediction is also relevant to computer vision (cs.CV), as it is often used in video analysis and other time-dependent image processing tasks.
